<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/55955360-nikita-maria-reclaiming-my-literacy"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1590438142i/55955360._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/55955360-nikita-maria-reclaiming-my-literacy">Nikita Maria (reclaiming my literacy)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I wish, but I also recognize that this will be incredibly difficult to adapt for two reasons:<br/>1. It&apos;ll be too &quot;sexual&quot; for Christian audiences<br/>2. It&apos;ll <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I wish, but I also recognize that this will be incredibly difficult to adapt for two reasons:<br />1. It'll be too "sexual" for Christian audiences<br />2. It'll be too Christian for secular audiences<br /><br />If you want to keep the movie somewhere in the ballpark of PG-13, a good deal of content will need to be cut--or the directors/editors will have to be creative in how they navigate those scenes. Even as a reader, there are certain scenes that made me blush, and I'm a New Yorker (virtually nothing makes us blush anymore). If anything, I could see this going the same route as The Red Tent and being adapted as a mini-series for a network like Lifetime, no more than 4 parts. The sad thing is that a lot of the spiritual content might get toned down in the process...I'd be more in favor of a Christian production company buying the rights and figuring out how to navigate the "sex scenes." If fans of the book watch the movie and complain about the toned down sexual content (which isn't graphic in the book to begin with), then it goes to show where their priorities are. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
