<div id="review_27269176" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/27269176" />
    <a title="Kathy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1075341-kathy"><img alt="Kathy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590589823p2/1075341.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/27269176?book_show_action=true">Jul 14, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathy" href="/user/show/1075341-kathy">Kathy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1075341-kathy?shelf=historical-american">historical-american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1075341-kathy?shelf=married-couple">married-couple</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1075341-kathy?shelf=rated-pg13">rated-pg13</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1075341-kathy?shelf=abuse">abuse</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1075341-kathy?shelf=christian-fiction">christian-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1075341-kathy?shelf=drama">drama</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer27269176" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer580370787694314179">I think the purpose of this book was overshadowed by the very dark subject matter. A lot of people have called this a Christian Romance, I find that very hard to believe. The story is about a young girl sold into prostitution at the age of eight who later is rescued by a man named Michael. The books goes into shocking, disturbing detail of the sad life she led. She run’s away from her devoted husband multiple times, which also got old. The whole thing was very depressing and I only continued to </span>
  <span id="freeText580370787694314179" style="display:none">I think the purpose of this book was overshadowed by the very dark subject matter. A lot of people have called this a Christian Romance, I find that very hard to believe. The story is about a young girl sold into prostitution at the age of eight who later is rescued by a man named Michael. The books goes into shocking, disturbing detail of the sad life she led. She run’s away from her devoted husband multiple times, which also got old. The whole thing was very depressing and I only continued to read hoping it would get better. I also didn’t like that her husband was suppose to be so understanding yet was still sleeping with her before she even loved him or before they really had a decent relationship. If he really had respect for her and what she had been through he would have waited until she was ready. The book was way too long and way too gloomy. For the subject matter and details given, I would give it an R rating. I wish I hadn’t bothered reading it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="580370787694314179" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
